  "target_response": {
    "text": "HRV measures the small variations in timing between heartbeats while you sleep. Broadly, higher does mean better readiness — it signals your recovery systems are in charge — but only relative to your own baseline; comparing against other people is meaningless because normal ranges differ hugely from person to person. Against your own history, 81 ms is an excellent reading: your 30-day average is 72.4, so you're sitting well above it, and the supporting cast agrees — resting heart rate at 51 bpm versus a usual 54, recovery at 82%. One caution: a sudden extreme HRV spike right after unusually hard stress can occasionally be noise rather than fitness. Today's isn't extreme — it's simply a good day, and a fine one for quality training.",
